This paper involves the use of deep reinforcement learning to predict the likelihood of an individual testing positive for malaria by asking questions about their household. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves the use of computational methods to survey households, which could fall under the sub-categories of Cybernetics (cs.CY) and Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE). Finally, the paper involves the use of data analysis and prediction, which could fall under the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
